#### Route Color System

9 predefined colors cycle for multi-trip display:

```typescript
const ROUTE_COLORS = [
  '#2563EB', // Blue
  '#DC2626', // Red
  '#16A34A', // Green
  '#D97706', // Amber
  '#7C3AED', // Purple
  '#0891B2', // Cyan
  '#DB2777', // Pink
  '#EA580C', // Orange
  '#4B5563', // Slate
];
```

Each trip is assigned `ROUTE_COLORS[index % 9]` for both the route polyline and numbered waypoint markers.

#### Marker Types

| Mode | `showNumbers=true` | `showNumbers=false` |
|------|-------------------|---------------------|
| Waypoints | `L.divIcon` with numbered pin (teardrop shape) | `L.circleMarker` (small dot) |
| Vehicle | SVG delivery truck icon (`L.divIcon`) | Same |

#### Playback System

The playback system supports both single and multi-trip modes:

| Control | Single Trip | Multi Trip |
|---------|------------|------------|
| ▶️ Play | Animates vehicle along route coordinates | Animates all active vehicles simultaneously |
| ⏸️ Pause | Stops interval | Same |
| ⏹️ Stop | Stops + disables nav buttons | Same |
| ⏩ Forward | Step-by-step forward with speed control | All vehicles step forward |
| ⏪ Backward | Step-by-step backward | All vehicles step backward |
| 🔄 Reset | Returns to start position | All vehicles return to start |
| Speed | 0.5x – 5x via select dropdown | Same |

**Deviation Detection** (Single trip only): If vehicle position deviates > 100m from the route, an alert is triggered.

#### Sidebar Content

**Single Trip Mode** (when `ids.length === 1`):
- Trip header (trip number, route code, date, session)
- Summary grid (12 items): start/end time, total time, start/end KM, driver, vehicle, route code, distance, customer count, sales value, receipt value
- Financial summary: opening balance, closing balance
- Playback controls
- Filter tabs: All / Sales / Delivery Notes / Collection / Counter
- Timeline: scrollable list of waypoint cards with bill details

**Multi Trip Mode** (when `ids.length > 1`):
- "Routes On Map" header with gradient
- Playback controls
- Scrollable route cards with:
  - Trip number, route code, vehicle, driver, checkpoint count
  - Color indicator dot matching route color
  - Enable/disable toggle switch per route
  - Click to drill into single trip view

#### Map Cleanup (Bug Fix Applied)

**File**: [trip-map-view.tsx](file:///c:/ASM%20Project/Git/ASM-Sales-React/Sales-web/src/sections/trip-creation/trip-map-view.tsx#L457-L510)

The `useEffect` cleanup follows a strict order to prevent `removeLayer` errors:

```
1. Clear all playback intervals (play, forward, backward)
2. Remove moving markers from map (with try/catch per marker)
3. Remove routing controls (with try/catch per control)
   - Unbind event handlers
   - Guard: check control._map exists
   - Clear waypoints before remove
   - Call control.remove()
4. Destroy the map instance (with try/catch)
5. Null all refs
```

> [!WARNING]
> The `useEffect` depends on `[allTripsData, filter, showNumbers, disabledTripIds, ids, loading]`. Any of these changing will tear down and rebuild the entire map. This is by design since Leaflet routing machine doesn't support dynamic route updates.

